00:09:54.159 --> 00:10:00.239
type, providing context where needed. The more the model knows about the columns and their types,

00:10:00.239 --> 00:10:07.520
the better SQL it generates. Now, you don't have to provide this extra information. If you don't,

00:10:07.520 --> 00:10:13.119
QueryChat will just send column names and types, and it lets the LLM figure out the rest.

00:10:14.320 --> 00:10:21.119
Finally, we can add some extra instructions too. And no surprises here, but we also provide these

00:10:21.119 --> 00:10:27.200
in a markdown file, and these instructions can further tweak the LLM's behavior. You can add

